The paper deals with distributed wireless networks and their connectivity, which falls under the category of Information Theory (cs.IT). It also involves the study of interference channels, which is a subfield of Networked Systems (cs.NI). The paper proposes a strategy for distributed decision-making, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper also involves the use of mathematical modeling and optimization techniques, which falls under the category of Mathematical Modeling (cs.MM) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
